250 g Ground Pork
170 g Coleslaw Cabbage Mix
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
28 g Crispy Shallots
1 tbsp Seasoned Rice Vinegar
4 tbsp Soy Sauce Mirin Blend
56 g Edamame
2 tbsp Spicy Mayo
28 g Peanuts, chopped
1 unit(s) Green Onion
0.06 tsp Salt*
0.06 tsp Pepper*
2 tsp Oil*

Core, then thinly slice pepper.
Thinly slice green onion.

Add vinegar and 1 tsp (2 tsp) oil to a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then whisk to combine.
Add peppers, coleslaw cabbage mix and half the green onions, then toss to coat.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When the pan is hot, add 1 tsp (2 tsp) oil, then pork.
Cook, breaking up pork into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.**

Add edamame and soy sauce mirin blend to the pan with pork.
Cook, stirring often, until sauce is absorbed, 5-6 min. (TIP: If you prefer a lighter glaze, add water, 1-2 tbsp at a time, until your desired consistency is reached.)

Divide slaw between plates.
Top with pork and edamame.
Drizzle with spicy mayo, then sprinkle crispy shallots, peanuts and remaining green onions over top.

If you've opted to get pork, cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the turkey.**